WEBVTT

00:02.570 --> 00:05.106
We were supposed
to recon the area
two hours ago.

00:05.173 --> 00:07.208
Meet's set for tonight.

00:07.275 --> 00:10.211
Yeah.
Couldn't be helped.
A delay at customs.

00:10.278 --> 00:14.748
- Hoo. That's a lot of euros.
- That's what
Alexander the Great said.

00:14.815 --> 00:16.784
I'm the one who had to sign
for the 32 million,

00:16.850 --> 00:19.820
so don't let me catch you
wearing Prada on the way home.

00:19.887 --> 00:21.789
Middle man takes two
for his cut.

00:21.855 --> 00:25.859
Petrov doesn't show his face
until the local guy
checks you out.

00:25.926 --> 00:29.463
- Let's make up for lost time.
- I think I got
your sizes right.

00:29.530 --> 00:32.133
It'll help you
fit in better.
Fit in where?

00:32.200 --> 00:34.135
The middle man, Dragan--
he operates a club.

00:34.202 --> 00:36.504
- We'll take it from here.
- It's not a gay club.

00:36.570 --> 00:39.673
To hop the rope,
you'll need arm candy.
That'd be me.

00:39.740 --> 00:43.111
- ** [ Dance ]
- [ Man Shouting
In Foreign Language ]

00:43.177 --> 00:46.314
** [ Sound System: Man Singing
In English, Indistinct ]

00:48.916 --> 00:52.520
[ Patrons Shouting,
Chattering ]

00:56.090 --> 01:01.095
* But you are on your way now
Come alive, come alive *

01:01.162 --> 01:05.032
* Come alive, come alive *

01:05.099 --> 01:08.836
* Come alive, come alive *

01:08.902 --> 01:12.840
* Come alive, come alive *

01:19.513 --> 01:24.051
Corner of the bar--
maroon shirt,
gold chain.

01:24.118 --> 01:26.254
Oh, yeah.

01:27.455 --> 01:30.424
** [ Continues, Indistinct ]

01:47.908 --> 01:50.211
Dragan?
Yes. Sizwe?

01:50.278 --> 01:52.112
Yes.
Pleasure to meet you.

01:52.180 --> 01:54.648
[ African Accent ]
Good to meet you.
Let's do some business.

02:04.692 --> 02:06.694
How long are you
staying in Kosovo?

02:06.760 --> 02:09.297
Just long enough for us
to conduct our business.

02:13.867 --> 02:16.570
- You know the price.
- I am prepared to pay.

02:16.637 --> 02:19.940
It's a lot of cash
for a little African country.

02:20.007 --> 02:23.611
It's not a lot of cash to me.
Do you want to count my money
or do business?

02:25.579 --> 02:27.381
All right.

02:27.448 --> 02:32.520
I can have Petrov, tomorrow,
here with your package.
So where is the money?

02:32.586 --> 02:36.156
When I get the plutonium.
And I need to test it.

02:36.224 --> 02:39.993
It has already been tested.
It's Pu-239.

02:40.060 --> 02:42.763
Yes. Very reassuring.
Nonetheless.

02:42.830 --> 02:45.132
You worry too much.
No.

02:45.199 --> 02:47.535
You see the money
when I see Petrov.

02:47.601 --> 02:51.672
He doesn't like
to be fooled with.
Neither do I. Tomorrow?

02:54.007 --> 02:56.744
Tomorrow.

02:56.810 --> 02:59.847
But tonight,
you will stay as my guest.

02:59.913 --> 03:03.384
Are you hungry
or thirsty?
No. I'm fine, thank you.

03:03.451 --> 03:07.187
Well, I would like to show you
some hospitality.

03:07.255 --> 03:09.257
You're my new friend, right?
Of course.

03:09.323 --> 03:11.459
Follow me.

03:18.399 --> 03:22.736
And this is?
A gesture
of good faith.

03:22.803 --> 03:25.639
Just like that?

03:25.706 --> 03:28.041
Anything you want.
She does it all.

03:28.108 --> 03:31.979
Backwards, forwards,
upside down.

03:32.045 --> 03:33.947
[ Snaps Fingers ]

03:36.083 --> 03:37.918
Whatever he likes.

03:42.823 --> 03:44.925
Okay?

03:46.460 --> 03:48.729
More than okay.

03:48.796 --> 03:50.698
Okay.

03:55.336 --> 03:57.237
First, tell me your name.

03:57.305 --> 04:00.040
Dava.
Dava.

04:00.107 --> 04:01.909
How long have you
worked here, Dava?

04:01.975 --> 04:04.712
Two months.

04:04.778 --> 04:06.614
Wait.

04:06.680 --> 04:09.550
But-But Dragan said--
I know what Dragan said.

04:09.617 --> 04:11.785
But my religion prevents me,

04:11.852 --> 04:16.324
as it also prevents me
from refusing a gift
from my host.

04:16.390 --> 04:19.460
So please, just--

04:20.461 --> 04:22.530
just sit down.

04:31.271 --> 04:33.441
You-You seem like
nice man.

04:38.178 --> 04:40.047
But others are not so.

04:42.916 --> 04:44.785
I would never hurt you.

04:49.823 --> 04:53.026
- But will you help me?
- If I were able to.

04:55.829 --> 04:59.500
My friend Nadia and I,
we come to Kosovo
to be models.

04:59.567 --> 05:01.769
But when we get here,

05:01.835 --> 05:04.372
he take our passport,
he beat us.
Dragan?

05:07.274 --> 05:10.478
He keep us here.
There are others?

05:10.544 --> 05:14.682
Some he sell.
Some he make work here.

05:14.748 --> 05:18.919
My friend Nadia,
she's very sick.

05:18.986 --> 05:22.790
If we don't
get out of here soon,
she will die in this hell.

05:22.856 --> 05:24.792
Will you help us?

05:26.427 --> 05:29.597
** [ Electronic Dance ]

05:42.943 --> 05:44.845
Trouble.

05:48.749 --> 05:50.818
[ Speaking
Foreign Language ]

05:50.884 --> 05:54.722
Who are they?
They're here
for the plutonium too.

05:54.788 --> 05:57.791
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]
Terrorist arms brokers.

05:57.858 --> 06:00.127
Looks like our sale
just turned into an auction.

06:00.193 --> 06:03.931
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

06:03.997 --> 06:08.035
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

06:08.101 --> 06:10.103
* See another dawn *

06:10.170 --> 06:12.239
* Through a daughter's eyes *

06:12.305 --> 06:16.744
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

06:28.489 --> 06:30.924
[ Monitor: Rhythmic Beeping ]

06:34.127 --> 06:37.798
Doctor. You feelin' any better?

06:37.865 --> 06:40.133
When do I move
to a real hospital?

06:40.200 --> 06:42.836
About that--
You got my results.

06:42.903 --> 06:46.273
It's as you thought.
Radiation specialist
is on his way now.

06:46.339 --> 06:48.341
I can save him the trip.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.811
Filgastrim
for the white blood cell count,

06:50.878 --> 06:53.447
potassium iodide
for the thyroid...

06:53.514 --> 06:56.750
and promethazine hydrochloride
for the nausea.

06:56.817 --> 06:59.887
Unless you can find me
something-- [ Laughs ]
herbal.

06:59.953 --> 07:02.355
They don't dispense
that medication on base.

07:02.422 --> 07:04.758
My question is this.
Were you poisoned
by the plutonium,

07:04.825 --> 07:07.294
or did you just
get sloppy in the lab?

07:07.360 --> 07:09.663
It's an occupational hazard.

07:09.730 --> 07:12.265
If your occupation
is terrorism.

07:12.332 --> 07:14.902
I was paid
to test their isotopes.

07:14.968 --> 07:18.706
I'd like to believe you.
We still think that you're
a valuable asset.

07:18.772 --> 07:22.075
I'm sure you do.
But I don't wish
to spend my last weeks--

07:23.443 --> 07:26.847
or days--
locked up in here.

07:26.914 --> 07:28.849
Client didn't tell you how he
planned to use the plutonium?

07:28.916 --> 07:31.519
No, but I gather
from what you've told me,

07:31.585 --> 07:34.588
he'll sell it to someone
who plans to make quite
a large bomb.

07:34.655 --> 07:36.724
You gather that, do you?

07:38.025 --> 07:41.795
When will I be moved
to a regular hospital?

07:41.862 --> 07:44.464
You'll have your chance
to see your Mr. Petrov again.

07:45.833 --> 07:48.569
You have broken our agreement!
You are insulting my country.

07:48.636 --> 07:52.372
What can I tell you,
my friend? It happens.

07:52.439 --> 07:53.941
When did
this other buyer appear?

07:54.007 --> 07:56.777
There are always buyers
for a product like this.

07:56.844 --> 07:59.813
- He is willing to pay more.
- How much more?

07:59.880 --> 08:02.015
Five million more.
No.

08:02.082 --> 08:04.752
No. I will not be
your stalking horse.

08:06.219 --> 08:08.021
The free market, my friend.

08:11.592 --> 08:13.694
I need more time.

08:15.262 --> 08:18.566
I'm on your side. But Petrov,
he doesn't like to wait.

08:18.632 --> 08:22.703
I can beat their offer.
I need time.

08:27.708 --> 08:29.743
How did you like the girl?

08:31.745 --> 08:34.481
She served her purpose.
Too old, huh?

08:34.548 --> 08:37.217
I have a 14-year-old
if you want.

08:38.719 --> 08:42.255
That is very thoughtful
of you, but I must decline.

08:45.959 --> 08:49.296
We got no time to dummy up
a wire transfer.

08:49.362 --> 08:53.967
What about the agency?
Mmm. We're barred from contact
with the station.

08:54.034 --> 08:57.838
We'd do better going
for my cutout account.
For five million euros?

08:57.905 --> 09:00.641
What do we use for collateral--
my old DeSoto?

09:00.708 --> 09:02.676
The black market's laying out
38 mil for nukes.

09:02.743 --> 09:05.579
They already got their
buyers standing by-- either
narco-terrorists or Al-Qaeda.

09:05.646 --> 09:08.782
- So where do we find
these new players?
- We know they're in town.

09:08.849 --> 09:11.985
And that they're well guarded--
sitting on all that cash.

09:12.052 --> 09:14.955
So how did our winning ways
compete with all that cash?

09:15.022 --> 09:18.558
Can't outspend 'em.
Must outthink 'em.

09:18.626 --> 09:20.594
Outspend 'em
or outshoot 'em.

09:20.661 --> 09:22.696
Does that include Dragan?

09:22.763 --> 09:26.934
- Starting with Dragan.
The man's scum.
- Yeah, but he's our scum.

09:27.000 --> 09:30.437
Besides plutonium, he traffics
in girls-- most of them younger
than my daughter.

09:30.503 --> 09:35.008
If we stay with Dragan, he may
lead us to the other buyers.
Eventually perhaps.

09:35.075 --> 09:37.577
Hold on. We don't have
to do the recon ourselves.

09:37.645 --> 09:41.048
There are others
who might want to help us.
[ Bob ] Others?

09:41.114 --> 09:44.017
Yeah. Those who might want
a favor in return.

09:44.084 --> 09:46.219
** [ Dance ]
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

10:08.676 --> 10:11.311
I came back for you.

10:17.050 --> 10:21.822
I need your help.
How can I help you?

10:23.590 --> 10:26.159
There's a man at the bar
with Dragan.

10:26.226 --> 10:31.231
I need to know something
about him and his friends--
an address.

10:33.633 --> 10:36.403
You-- You want me to--
I don't care how.

10:40.173 --> 10:42.810
But if I do this--
Then I will help you.

10:45.445 --> 10:50.483
Your friend Nadia,
is she the one
stuck to Dragan's side?

10:50.550 --> 10:52.419
Then I will get you both out.

11:10.938 --> 11:14.241
One for you,
Mrs. Bechet.

11:14.307 --> 11:18.411
-Uh, another for you, Mrs. Dahl.
-[ Molly ]
It's like Christmas come early.

11:18.478 --> 11:20.981
- [ Tiffy ]
Is there any cash in here?
- You're asking the wrong guy.

11:21.048 --> 11:24.117
I'm just the pony express.

11:24.184 --> 11:27.054
Lookin'.

11:31.458 --> 11:34.762
[ Tiffy ]
My own California
teaching certificate.

11:34.828 --> 11:38.365
I'm back in the classroom.
Oh, my God.

11:38.431 --> 11:41.134
- And I start this morning.
- At least you won't
have to fake it.

11:41.201 --> 11:43.771
Vice President of Marketing,
AeroDyne Alliance.

11:43.837 --> 11:47.140
I'm still waiting to find out
what this Alliance
actually makes.

11:47.207 --> 11:49.476
What we make
or what we say we make?

11:51.344 --> 11:53.180
Aircraft engines.

11:54.581 --> 11:57.217
Custom appliances.

11:57.284 --> 12:00.720
- Our new base of operations.
- Our new clubhouse.

12:01.654 --> 12:03.523
Don't expect me to sweep up.

12:03.590 --> 12:07.227
Why do I feel like
the girl with the glasses
at the homecoming dance?

12:07.294 --> 12:10.130
I'm sure
it's not deliberate.
Everything here is deliberate.

12:10.197 --> 12:12.866
Taking my kids away from me
was deliberate.

12:12.933 --> 12:15.969
There's no good
in complaining.

12:16.036 --> 12:18.571
It's unfair.
It's unfortunate.

12:18.638 --> 12:21.408
It's regrettable.
It's tragic.

12:21.474 --> 12:25.745
But it's not unfair.
The army's trying
to keep us safe.

12:25.813 --> 12:28.481
Maybe they're still
working out your cover.

12:30.250 --> 12:32.219
And maybe I'm better off
without one.

12:32.285 --> 12:34.454
We're all going
to make it through this.

12:38.258 --> 12:41.594
Lissy! Lis!
Hey, hey. Hey, wait up.

12:41.661 --> 12:44.764
I heard you, Mom.
Well, you didn't
let me finish.

12:44.832 --> 12:48.468
I get it.
You didn't ask
for this job.

12:48.535 --> 12:50.770
Can we talk about this later?

12:50.838 --> 12:53.406
Well, look at it this way.
We're both new here.

12:53.473 --> 12:57.677
At least now we can
look out for each other.
I don't need looking after.

12:57.744 --> 12:59.813
Just to keep our stories
straight.

12:59.880 --> 13:03.183
I'm not gonna blow our cover
like you almost did.

13:03.250 --> 13:05.953
Now, come on.
Let's try and be nice
to each other, huh?

13:06.019 --> 13:08.555
Look, I'll see you
after school.

13:08.621 --> 13:10.891
[ Class Bell Rings ]
Oh!

13:10.958 --> 13:13.226
Man, I am so sorry.
Really.

13:13.293 --> 13:16.864
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm all right.
Just get to class.

13:17.865 --> 13:19.766
[ Kids Chattering,
Laughing ]

13:19.833 --> 13:21.534
- [ Sighs ]
- [ Phone Rings ]

13:21.601 --> 13:23.971
[ Beeps ]
Hello?

13:24.037 --> 13:27.107
This is Jessica at the agency
confirming your interview
this afternoon.

13:27.174 --> 13:29.209
I'm sorry.
You have
the wrong number.

13:29.276 --> 13:31.278
Kim Cahill?

13:31.344 --> 13:35.448
It is. Yes, but--
I have your employment card
right here.

13:35.515 --> 13:39.452
Your interview's at 1:00.
The interview. Oh.

13:39.519 --> 13:42.689
A wonderful couple
with a teenage son
and an infant daughter.

13:42.755 --> 13:44.958
And what exactly
are they looking for?

13:45.025 --> 13:46.894
They need someone who can
start right away full-time.

13:46.960 --> 13:49.062
I see. But--

13:49.129 --> 13:52.032
They just lost their nanny,
and they're really in a bind.

13:53.333 --> 13:55.635
A nanny.

13:55.702 --> 13:57.704
Our old nanny quit,
out of nowhere.

13:57.770 --> 14:00.340
Just disappeared
without an explanation.

14:00.407 --> 14:02.910
So above all, we really need
someone we feel we can trust.

14:02.976 --> 14:06.914
Of course. Some people just
aren't cut out for children.
[ Baby Cooing ]

14:06.980 --> 14:10.951
Your references are excellent.
Looks like most of them
are from Kansas.

14:11.018 --> 14:14.287
That's right.
What brings you
to California?

14:14.354 --> 14:16.957
Uh, my husband's company
transferred him out here.

14:17.024 --> 14:19.059
Ah. What does he do
for work?

14:19.126 --> 14:22.295
He's in the private aircraft
business. Sales.

14:22.362 --> 14:25.298
Unfortunately,
he travels a lot.

14:25.365 --> 14:27.067
Oh, thanks.

14:27.134 --> 14:29.236
So that leaves me
with plenty of free time.

14:29.302 --> 14:32.005
My wife's always on the road
for work too.

14:32.072 --> 14:34.307
It's not easy with a newborn.
No, not easy for you.

14:36.543 --> 14:39.446
Oh. Looks like you've had
some experience with infants.

14:39.512 --> 14:43.350
Uh, I come from a big family--
nieces, nephews and a lot
of dirty diapers.

14:43.416 --> 14:47.020
[ Laughs ]
We also have
a 15-year-old. Lucas.

14:47.087 --> 14:49.022
He's a real jock.
Can't wait to meet him.

14:49.089 --> 14:51.424
How about this afternoon?
Excuse me?

14:51.491 --> 14:53.126
Can you start today?

14:53.193 --> 14:55.462
** [ Electronic Dance ]

14:55.528 --> 14:58.098
** [ Continues ]
[ Man Shouting, Chattering ]

15:12.812 --> 15:15.715
Did you get it?

15:15.782 --> 15:18.585
I told him he was so good
I wanted to see him
for free.

15:18.651 --> 15:20.920
Where is he staying?

15:23.823 --> 15:27.560
First, you help.
I need doctor.

15:27.627 --> 15:31.064
- After the doctor,
if you should run--
- I cannot run.

15:31.131 --> 15:34.001
As long as Dragan
has Nadia, I cannot run.

15:34.067 --> 15:36.169
Let's go.

15:39.606 --> 15:42.675
[ Softly ]
* Sound off, one, two *
[ Whimpering ]

15:42.742 --> 15:46.013
* Sound off, three, four **

15:47.814 --> 15:50.650
It works
for my little Emily too.

15:52.052 --> 15:53.987
[ Sniffles ]
Are you all right?

15:54.054 --> 15:57.724
[ Baby Whining ]
Oh. Hi.

15:57.790 --> 16:01.028
[ Chuckles ]
I'm sorry.

16:02.395 --> 16:04.897
It's just that my husband and I
have been trying so hard...

16:04.964 --> 16:08.801
to have one of our own and--
She's beautiful.

16:08.868 --> 16:12.272
- I understand.
- You do?

16:12.339 --> 16:16.343
Marian and I did fertility
treatments for six years.
It was rough.

16:16.409 --> 16:18.378
Harder than I thought.
Are you on a protocol?

16:18.445 --> 16:21.414
- Hmm?
- Fertility treatments.

16:21.481 --> 16:23.483
I had to give Marian shots
twice a day.

16:23.550 --> 16:26.386
Oh, yeah.
We're trying everything.

16:26.453 --> 16:28.588
How many c.c.'s
are you on?
Gosh.

16:28.655 --> 16:33.193
There's so many.
I get 'em all confused.

16:33.260 --> 16:35.862
It's the one
in the oil solution.
I became a real expert.

16:35.928 --> 16:39.566
To tell you the truth,
I let my husband be the expert.

16:39.632 --> 16:42.735
He says "Bottoms up,"
and I don't even look.

16:45.038 --> 16:48.341
It'll work out.
You're very kind.

16:48.408 --> 16:51.911
Hey, you know what they say.
Your children will find you.

16:51.978 --> 16:54.647
I hope so.

17:06.626 --> 17:10.430
Hey. Need any help?

17:10.497 --> 17:13.300
No, thanks.
I'm just waiting
for my daughter.

17:13.366 --> 17:16.269
Oh. Most everyone's
gone home already.
Yeah, looks that way.

17:16.336 --> 17:19.072
You want me
to go look for her?
No. It's okay.

17:19.139 --> 17:22.275
No. I'd be glad to.
It's not necessary, um--

17:22.342 --> 17:25.445
Josh. I didn't hurt you,
I hope?

17:25.512 --> 17:28.748
- A little whiplash is all.
- Oh, my God. I'm sorry.

17:28.815 --> 17:31.951
I'm kidding.
No, no. I had that kind
of injury last season.

17:32.018 --> 17:34.621
Right here.
I said it's not necessary.

17:34.687 --> 17:38.891
Make you feel better.
I beg your pardon?

17:38.958 --> 17:41.394
You never know.

17:43.062 --> 17:46.933
I think you'll be better off
focusing your attention
on girls your own age.

17:46.999 --> 17:50.403
Eh, the girls here
are immature.

17:50.470 --> 17:54.541
I prefer women.
Nothing like ambition.

17:54.607 --> 17:58.178
For example, you.

17:58.245 --> 18:00.380
I'm a teacher,
and you're a minor.

18:00.447 --> 18:02.582
I'm 18.
You're not hearing me,
Josh.

18:02.649 --> 18:04.851
It's against school policy,
and it's against the law.

18:04.917 --> 18:07.053
And it's against my wishes,
which I have made plain.

18:07.120 --> 18:10.022
So move on.

18:10.089 --> 18:12.659
Well, you don't have
to be a bitch about it.

18:12.725 --> 18:14.394
Good-bye, Josh.

18:14.461 --> 18:16.329
Ten years from now,
when that face is all cracked,

18:16.396 --> 18:18.931
you're gonna be thinking
about what you could've had.

18:18.998 --> 18:21.801
Get out of my sight.

18:26.105 --> 18:28.808
[ Engine Starts ]

18:42.322 --> 18:44.457
Someone was very rough
on that girl.
Mm-hmm.

18:44.524 --> 18:46.459
She says
you're her boyfriend.

18:46.526 --> 18:48.928
Just tell me
you can help her.

18:48.995 --> 18:50.963
I can, but it's involved.

18:51.030 --> 18:55.067
I see. So let us
make it simple.

18:55.134 --> 18:58.305
Hmm. I'll do what's possible.

18:58.371 --> 19:00.473
I'm sure you will.

19:03.410 --> 19:07.146
[ Doctor Shouting
In Foreign Language ]

19:08.615 --> 19:10.750
Let go of her.
She's a thief!

19:10.817 --> 19:12.685
Look! Show him.

19:13.920 --> 19:16.256
I will pay!
I will.

19:18.057 --> 19:20.092
Morphine?
Drug addict!

19:20.159 --> 19:22.562
It's not for me.
I swear.

19:22.629 --> 19:26.699
It's for Nadia.
She has AIDS.

19:26.766 --> 19:28.768
She always has pain.

19:40.780 --> 19:42.815
Let us go.

19:42.882 --> 19:45.718
[ Exhales ]

19:45.785 --> 19:48.255
[ TV Playing, Muffled ]

20:05.171 --> 20:08.541
[ Man ] Who's there?
[ Slavic Accent ]
Dragan sent me.

20:11.978 --> 20:13.813
For his best clients.

20:29.729 --> 20:32.465
Dragan saved the best
for last.

20:32.532 --> 20:35.302
Maybe you had
to prove yourselves.

20:35.368 --> 20:37.203
How do you
prove yourself?

20:37.270 --> 20:39.439
Me?

20:41.474 --> 20:43.510
I am a specialist.

20:43.576 --> 20:45.578
Good. Because I got
something special for you.

20:45.645 --> 20:48.981
First, get me a drink,
will you?

20:56.623 --> 20:59.892
You have a lovely view.

20:59.959 --> 21:01.928
We're out of ice.

21:01.994 --> 21:05.231
Good. I like it warm.

21:05.298 --> 21:07.367
Where's your accent from?

21:09.201 --> 21:12.104
You want small talk,
get a girlfriend.

21:12.171 --> 21:13.973
I don't have time
for it.

21:16.909 --> 21:20.246
- Feel good?
- Mmm.

21:20.313 --> 21:23.816
Now it's my turn.
Sure is.

21:24.884 --> 21:26.486
[ Laughs ]

21:29.456 --> 21:30.723
[ Door Slams ]

21:38.197 --> 21:41.568
- Clear.
- Clear.

21:41.634 --> 21:44.371
By the couch.
I got it.

21:46.406 --> 21:48.641
[ Grunts ]

21:51.811 --> 21:53.646
Here.

22:00.252 --> 22:01.788
[ Lock Snaps ]

22:06.325 --> 22:08.461
[ Exhales ]

22:08.528 --> 22:11.664
They make money
the old-fashioned way.
They steal it.

22:12.699 --> 22:15.402
I guess the bidding's closed.

22:20.607 --> 22:22.642
Lucky for you, huh?

22:22.709 --> 22:24.644
Maybe they found
another deal elsewhere.

22:24.711 --> 22:26.546
They didn't drop out
from the bidding.

22:26.613 --> 22:28.981
They dropped dead.

22:29.048 --> 22:32.585
Look, these things
happen, my friend,
in a free market economy.

22:32.652 --> 22:35.822
But I don't think that
Petrov is gonna sell you
this plutonium on the cheap.

22:35.888 --> 22:38.357
Where I come from,
32 million is not cheap.

22:38.425 --> 22:40.292
[ Slams Glass ]

22:40.359 --> 22:43.095
Thirty-seven million.
That was the price.

22:43.162 --> 22:45.665
Thirty-seven million.

22:45.732 --> 22:48.234
When you had two bidders.
Now you have only the one.

22:48.300 --> 22:50.737
One who will pay 37 million.

22:50.803 --> 22:52.805
And they want
your assurance...

22:52.872 --> 22:56.208
that no one else
in this transaction
drops out.

22:56.275 --> 22:58.645
- [ Door Opens ]
- [ Chattering ]

23:02.582 --> 23:04.651
I believe we have a deal.

23:05.885 --> 23:08.020
Hey, I'm still not
getting the uplink.

23:08.087 --> 23:10.156
Will you check
your L.N.B. connection?

23:10.222 --> 23:12.559
Try doubling back the wire
before you hit the solder.

23:15.862 --> 23:17.930
[ Beeps ]
Yeah. I got it.

23:19.298 --> 23:21.100
Up and ready for business here.

23:22.301 --> 23:24.504
[ Bridget ]
Great.

23:24.571 --> 23:27.640
While you're at it,
you can put chrome rims on.
Then we'll really get noticed.

23:27.707 --> 23:30.910
Redcap, don't teach
your grandmother
how to suck eggs.

23:32.679 --> 23:36.516
Now we're just another
wandering band of gypsies.

23:38.350 --> 23:40.419
Smile, Bridge,
for your home page.

23:41.554 --> 23:43.856
Slavic lethargy.
What do you think?

23:43.923 --> 23:45.892
Eh. How about something
a little more viral?

23:45.958 --> 23:48.895
What do you want me to do,
blow 'em a kiss.

23:48.961 --> 23:50.830
Yeah. They'll
love that in the TOC.
Nah.

23:50.897 --> 23:52.699
Colonel Ryan's not much
of a romantic, huh?

23:58.971 --> 24:01.508
What?

24:05.311 --> 24:08.515
Let's throw this thing together.
We got a half an hour
to get in place.

24:11.050 --> 24:13.185
Yes?

24:13.252 --> 24:16.222
Oh. I just got a call
from the office.
I have to go in today.

24:16.288 --> 24:18.958
- You want me to stay
with Ella?
- If you don't mind.

24:19.025 --> 24:21.494
I'm sorry. I thought
I was gonna be able
to work from home today.

24:21.561 --> 24:24.263
I can stay
as long as you want.

24:24.330 --> 24:26.833
- I--
- I'll watch her
as if she were my own.

24:26.899 --> 24:31.538
Let me give you my cell number
just in case you need anything.

24:36.042 --> 24:39.011
I can't tell you
how grateful I am.

24:39.078 --> 24:40.947
Don't worry.

24:44.116 --> 24:46.085
Okay.

24:50.422 --> 24:53.693
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

25:00.533 --> 25:03.102
I need to get used to
the developmental approach
out here.

25:03.169 --> 25:06.539
If you ever have a problem
with the curriculum,
feel free to stop by my office.

25:06.606 --> 25:09.742
Would you excuse me?
I see a student of mine
I need to speak with.

25:12.111 --> 25:14.313
What are you doing?
Going to class.

25:14.380 --> 25:16.616
I thought you said
the girls out here
were too immature for you.

25:16.683 --> 25:19.385
Mmm, Lissy's cool.
She's 16.

25:19.451 --> 25:21.287
And she is not for you.

25:21.353 --> 25:24.290
Okay, she's too young for me.
You're too old for me.

25:24.356 --> 25:27.126
Let's try this.
You date who you want,
Lissy dates who she wants.

25:27.193 --> 25:31.430
All right. You're a predator.
And you're looking for a victim.

25:31.497 --> 25:33.566
I understand.
I am not a victim.

25:33.633 --> 25:35.602
You think I'm an easy mark?
I will correct you.

25:35.668 --> 25:38.638
Stay away
from my daughter and me.

25:38.705 --> 25:41.774
Well, if you weren't
making it so hard,
I wouldn't have to go that way.

25:41.841 --> 25:46.345
Let's get this straight. If
I find you anywhere near Lissy,
I will make you regret it.

25:46.412 --> 25:50.316
Oh. I could report you
to the principal for using
threatening language.

25:50.382 --> 25:53.052
I mean,
it is against school policy
and against the law.

25:53.119 --> 25:55.822
Do you want me
to take this to the office?
What are you gonna say--

25:55.888 --> 25:58.524
that I hit on you yesterday
and you didn't report it
immediately as required?

25:58.591 --> 26:02.061
And then I'd tell
the principal that the reason
you kept your mouth shut...

26:02.128 --> 26:07.033
was because you hit on me,
threatened me if I told anyone.

26:12.004 --> 26:14.907
Oh, and now
I have an eyewitness.

26:14.974 --> 26:17.109
Maybe I should
just go tell her myself.

26:17.176 --> 26:22.581
Or we could...
work something out.

26:24.216 --> 26:26.085
[ Pops Lips ]

26:30.923 --> 26:34.193
[ Siren Wailing
In Distance ]

26:44.603 --> 26:47.306
Dirt Diver, we're in place.
[ Mack On Radio ]
We're in position.

26:47.373 --> 26:50.609
No one moves on Petrov until
we've got a positive I.D.

26:52.411 --> 26:57.884
- [ Radio Chatter ]
- [ Bob On Radio ]
Snake Doc's got company.

26:57.950 --> 26:59.852
Please.

27:01.688 --> 27:05.892
I hope you don't mind
that I took the liberty
of ordering some espresso.

27:05.958 --> 27:08.127
Thank you.
Thank you.

27:12.364 --> 27:16.268
I have 37 million reasons
why we should conclude
our business today.

27:16.335 --> 27:18.771
I will have to see
those 37 million reasons.

27:18.838 --> 27:21.841
Cool Breeze,
this is Dogpatch 0-6.

27:21.908 --> 27:25.111
We got a clear transmission,
but we can't get a positive I.D.

27:25.177 --> 27:27.914
Roger that, Dogpatch.
Comin' your way
most rikki-tik.

27:29.782 --> 27:32.284
[ Whirring ]

27:37.389 --> 27:40.126
Redcap, we're rollin'.
I need a look my way, please.

27:43.295 --> 27:46.098
[ Petrov ]
There is location.
We need a little bit of time.

27:46.165 --> 27:48.735
How much time?

27:51.838 --> 27:53.139
Eh.
[ Muttering ]

27:53.205 --> 27:56.508
[ Ryan ]
Got it. Great!
Run it! Print it!

27:56.575 --> 28:00.312
Dirt Diver, stand by.
We're gonna get
your confirmation.

28:00.379 --> 28:02.214
Is that him?

28:05.417 --> 28:08.921
- No. I don't recognize him.
- That's not Petrov?

28:11.724 --> 28:13.793
I've never
seen this man before.

28:19.498 --> 28:21.768
Dirt Diver,
we got a situation.

28:21.834 --> 28:24.336
That man with Snake Doctor
is not Petrov.

28:24.403 --> 28:27.173
I repeat.
[ On Radio ]
That is not our target.

28:32.678 --> 28:36.648
[ Man ] We have deal, yes?
[ Jonas ]
Yes, as soon as we can see--

28:36.715 --> 28:39.451
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]
No, thank you.

28:39.518 --> 28:41.587
[ Speaking
Foreign Language ]

28:41.653 --> 28:43.322
You want.
You want.
No!

28:49.061 --> 28:52.932
[ Dragan Speaking
Foreign Language ]

28:54.300 --> 28:56.168
Here. Go!

29:03.709 --> 29:06.879
Okay. We have
come to the terms.
Let's get the package.

29:06.946 --> 29:11.283
Hold. How do I know
that he is who he says?

29:11.350 --> 29:15.421
- Who do you think I am?
- I was told to deal
only with Petrov.

29:15.487 --> 29:17.924
He's got what you need.
That's who he is.

29:17.990 --> 29:20.226
You lied to me!
Who is this man?

29:20.292 --> 29:22.895
How do you know
that this is not Petrov?

29:22.962 --> 29:25.664
Because you have
asked the question.

29:25.731 --> 29:27.466
Okay.

29:27.533 --> 29:31.703
He is not actually
Petrov.
I work for Petrov.

29:31.770 --> 29:33.505
You said Petrov himself.
Where is Petrov?

29:33.572 --> 29:37.844
He is-- It's just, Petrov,
he doesn't like, you know,
to expose himself.

29:37.910 --> 29:41.247
For 37 million,
he can dance naked
in the square!

29:41.313 --> 29:44.150
Until then, no deal.

29:44.216 --> 29:46.152
Taxi!

29:51.924 --> 29:54.793
No, no, no!
No, wait, wait!

29:59.731 --> 30:03.169
If he's delivering
a kilo of plutonium,

30:05.171 --> 30:07.239
he'll have it
divided up...

30:07.306 --> 30:11.878
into 15 to 20
individual pigs.

30:11.944 --> 30:14.146
[ Groaning ]

30:18.050 --> 30:22.221
Your man has
90 seconds exposure...

30:22.288 --> 30:25.457
before he risks
radiation poisoning.

30:25.524 --> 30:28.560
- But he has to test it?
- More than one pig.

30:30.629 --> 30:33.933
Sometimes they'll offer up
one good sample...

30:34.000 --> 30:37.403
from a lot of 30 losers.

30:37.469 --> 30:39.872
What's the threshold?

30:39.939 --> 30:42.174
Ninety-five percent purity.

30:42.241 --> 30:44.310
But it's good enough
to make a bomb.

30:44.376 --> 30:47.579
Perhaps.
Perhaps.

30:47.646 --> 30:50.616
If that kid files a complaint
with the principal--
A bogus complaint.

30:50.682 --> 30:54.553
Any complaint.
The school is required
to open an investigation.

30:54.620 --> 30:56.822
They'll dig
into my background,
and they'll crack my cover.

30:56.889 --> 30:59.992
And that opens the door
on all of us.
You need to slam that door.

31:00.059 --> 31:03.529
Has the boy gone
to the principal?

31:03.595 --> 31:06.865
No. But he's got me
in a corner,
and he knows it.

31:06.933 --> 31:11.737
Tiffy, the first thing
you learn in combat is
to assess the enemy's strength.

31:11.803 --> 31:13.272
What's he got?
You mean--

31:13.339 --> 31:15.074
I mean the threat.
An accusation.

31:15.141 --> 31:17.409
The weight of his words.

31:17.476 --> 31:19.979
In martial arts, we use
the enemy's own weight
against him--

31:20.046 --> 31:22.314
make him extend himself
until he's off balance.

31:22.381 --> 31:24.516
So you want me to what,
throw him?

31:24.583 --> 31:28.587
[ Laughs ]
Use what he's using
against himself.

31:28.654 --> 31:31.323
- The accusations?
- And anything else
you can bring to bear.

31:31.390 --> 31:34.927
Anything you can
to raise him out.
To get down on his level?

31:34.994 --> 31:37.964
No. Break his will to fight.

31:43.235 --> 31:45.237
I wasn't even doing
anything wrong.

31:45.304 --> 31:47.773
I don't care, Lissy.
Stay away from him.

31:47.839 --> 31:49.908
Why?
Because he's trouble.

31:49.976 --> 31:51.910
Because why, he's 18?

31:51.978 --> 31:54.346
It's more than that.

31:54.413 --> 31:59.118
He was the only one
who even talked to me
at school today, Mom.

31:59.185 --> 32:03.022
Remember on the bus ride here
when we were talking about
shared sacrifice,

32:03.089 --> 32:06.358
about making compromises
for the greater good?

32:06.425 --> 32:10.329
Well, this is one
of those sacrifices
I'm asking you to make.

32:10.396 --> 32:13.365
And I wouldn't ask
if it wasn't important.

32:15.101 --> 32:17.169
It's important.

32:28.080 --> 32:31.217
Here they are now.
[ Murmurs ]

32:31.283 --> 32:33.152
Good.

32:33.219 --> 32:36.288
[ Soldiers Speaking
Foreign Language ]

32:44.263 --> 32:47.366
Dragan, Petrov sent us.

32:47.433 --> 32:50.969
And where is he?
He said he was coming.

32:51.037 --> 32:53.072
[ Man Whistles ]

33:05.917 --> 33:09.155
Petrov, my brother.

33:15.794 --> 33:20.699
I am here, as requested.
Let's make this quick.

33:20.766 --> 33:23.635
NATO uniforms. Smart.

33:23.702 --> 33:26.072
It makes the border crossing
less stressful.

33:26.138 --> 33:28.207
Go ahead.

33:39.251 --> 33:41.253
[ Geiger Counter Beeps,
Ticking ]

33:50.562 --> 33:52.931
[ Ticking ]
Mmm.

33:52.998 --> 33:54.966
As promised.

33:55.033 --> 33:57.903
Now it is your turn.

33:57.969 --> 34:00.206
Thirty-seven million
is the price.

34:00.272 --> 34:04.943
That was the price...
before you fixed the bidding.

34:05.010 --> 34:07.179
Violence draws
too much attention.

34:07.246 --> 34:10.549
Authorities must be paid off.

34:12.484 --> 34:16.088
So it is going to cost you.

34:16.155 --> 34:19.825
Me? I brought you
this money.

34:19.891 --> 34:21.493
You also brought this danger.

34:21.560 --> 34:24.230
Take it from his cut.
No. He has no more cut.

34:24.296 --> 34:27.966
He owes me,
or no deal for anyone.

34:28.033 --> 34:30.602
- What do you want?
- Whatever is his.

34:30.669 --> 34:32.471
Drugs, girls.

34:32.538 --> 34:35.607
I am just
a small businessman.

34:35.674 --> 34:38.810
Oh, but you, of course, have
something that you've saved
for a rainy day.

34:40.546 --> 34:44.250
No? Fine. You want us
to find out for ourselves?

34:44.316 --> 34:46.952
[ Shouts Command ]

34:47.018 --> 34:48.787
Petrov, you don't want
to do this.

34:48.854 --> 34:51.923
What is this?

34:51.990 --> 34:54.293
A cost of doing business.

35:00.532 --> 35:03.001
Cool Breeze,
something's going down.
They got guns on Snake Doc.

35:03.068 --> 35:07.473
- What's with the soldiers
in the club?
- I don't know.

35:07.539 --> 35:09.441
What now?

35:09.508 --> 35:12.444
We just-- We hang back.
We want that plutonium.

35:17.449 --> 35:21.553
You were holding out
on us, Dragan.

35:21.620 --> 35:24.456
I will take
all of the girls
as payment.

35:24.523 --> 35:26.825
That's too far.
These girls are mine.

35:26.892 --> 35:29.328
If you want to drop out
of this deal over them, do it!

35:29.395 --> 35:32.531
- That's enough!
- Oh, really?
Because you say so?

35:32.598 --> 35:35.234
- [ Dragan Shouts ]
- [ Speaking Foreign Language ]

35:35.301 --> 35:38.069
Let us conclude
our business here.

35:38.136 --> 35:40.005
Forget this business.
Forget your money.

35:40.071 --> 35:42.508
I can find other buyers.

35:42.574 --> 35:46.478
- Thirty-seven million,
and you still need the girls?
- Well, it's my commission.

35:46.545 --> 35:48.647
You can't have my girls
without paying.

35:48.714 --> 35:52.484
- I want to close this deal.
- And I'd like to go home!

35:52.551 --> 35:55.221
- If he won't give them,
shoot them.
- [ Jonas ] Wait!

35:56.322 --> 35:58.757
Sell me the girls.
What?

35:58.824 --> 36:02.794
Done. Now they're mine.

36:02.861 --> 36:06.598
And now yours.

36:08.600 --> 36:11.903
Give me the keys.
We swap.

36:15.274 --> 36:17.843
[ Whimpers ]
Fine transaction.

36:17.909 --> 36:19.811
Yes.

36:19.878 --> 36:22.381
[ Soldier Speaking
Foreign Language ]

36:30.489 --> 36:32.691
[ Engine Starts ]

36:45.504 --> 36:50.242
I hope your country
appreciates your patriotism.
[ Scoffs ]

36:50.309 --> 36:51.977
[ Drops Accent ]
I hope so too.

37:03.355 --> 37:05.657
Tell Dirt Diver--
pick up the Saab.

37:05.724 --> 37:08.226
I want Petrov.
I don't care how.

37:08.294 --> 37:10.829
What about the money?
We go after the truck?

37:10.896 --> 37:15.066
No, we can't.
We gotta secure
the plutonium first.

37:15.133 --> 37:17.569
Then we get
the girls back.

37:26.978 --> 37:29.748
[ Jonas ] Push it.
They could've
crossed over by now.

37:29.815 --> 37:30.882
Push it.

37:33.452 --> 37:36.755
The border's
only six klicks out.
We can make it.

37:36.822 --> 37:39.958
- [ Mack On Radio ]
Cool Breeze.
- Go.

37:40.025 --> 37:42.328
Tell Snake Doc it's over.

37:43.895 --> 37:47.833
- Petrov?
- Didn't leave me a choice.

37:47.899 --> 37:49.835
What about the truck?
What about the girl?

37:49.901 --> 37:52.371
[ Mack ]
Negative.
No girls here, Top.

37:59.177 --> 38:02.147
We got Petrov.

38:02.213 --> 38:04.249
Good.

38:04.316 --> 38:06.785
Did he say anything?
About you?

38:08.320 --> 38:10.288
What do you want,
Colonel?

38:10.356 --> 38:12.524
I want to know
who hired you and why.

38:12.591 --> 38:15.594
Petrov sells nuclear materials
to the highest bidder.

38:15.661 --> 38:17.663
He doesn't care
who wants 'em and why.

38:17.729 --> 38:20.198
Nor does he hire academics
like you to vet his isotopes...

38:20.265 --> 38:23.502
when any out-of-work
Russian lab rat
can do it on the cheap.

38:23.569 --> 38:26.472
Now he was paid to get you
bomb-grade plutonium.

38:26.538 --> 38:29.074
And I'm asking you
one more time--
for whom?

38:29.140 --> 38:31.810
Why don't you ask Petrov?

38:31.877 --> 38:34.413
Petrov's dead.

38:34.480 --> 38:36.415
Well, so am I.

38:36.482 --> 38:38.717
Not yet you're not.

38:38.784 --> 38:41.587
Save what's left
of your life.

38:42.588 --> 38:45.323
It's not my life
that matters now.

38:48.860 --> 38:50.796
[ Kids Chattering ]

38:54.265 --> 38:58.003
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

38:58.069 --> 39:01.840
[ Chattering ]
Fellas.

39:19.357 --> 39:21.627
I made a mistake
not coming to you first.

39:21.693 --> 39:24.896
But being new here,
I just didn't want
to be hard on the boy.

39:24.963 --> 39:27.933
Okay. But you were
clear with him about
the sexual harassment?

39:27.999 --> 39:30.636
In no uncertain terms.
That's why he came after me...

39:30.702 --> 39:33.439
and threatened me
with physical violence
when I said no.

39:33.505 --> 39:35.707
Frankly,
I'm still a little scared.

39:35.774 --> 39:38.577
These days, you have to take
every potential threat
seriously.

39:38.644 --> 39:40.311
Absolutely.
[ Knocking ]

39:40.378 --> 39:43.449
You're needed right away
at the east entrance.
There's a serious situation.

39:44.483 --> 39:46.585
Excuse me.

39:51.189 --> 39:53.459
[ All Chattering ]

39:54.526 --> 39:56.628
What happened?
Mrs. Green, it's not mine.

39:56.695 --> 39:58.697
What?
The metal detector
went off.

39:58.764 --> 40:00.699
We found a handgun
on him.
It's not mine. I swear.

40:00.766 --> 40:02.768
I don't know
how it got there!
In the office.

40:02.834 --> 40:05.136
Get the police down here.
Now.
No! Wait!

40:10.676 --> 40:13.311
[ Guard ]
"F" you, young man.
You stay right there.

40:13.378 --> 40:15.481
Thank you.

40:16.482 --> 40:18.584
For the greater good.

40:20.351 --> 40:22.353
Who else
got these brochures?

40:22.420 --> 40:25.857
They're only for the showroom.
We received a hundred
for display.

40:25.924 --> 40:28.827
Then why does
my new employer have one?

40:28.894 --> 40:31.830
One of those?
Are you sure?

40:31.897 --> 40:34.833
Saw it right on his desk.
The number was circled.

40:34.900 --> 40:37.503
A voice on the phone tells me
to interview with him,

40:37.569 --> 40:39.505
and he's got this
in his house.

40:39.571 --> 40:41.607
Who is he?
His name's Isaac Reed.

40:41.673 --> 40:43.542
He's in the import-export
business.

40:43.609 --> 40:47.513
Why would he have a brochure
from us when we don't
technically exist yet?

40:47.579 --> 40:49.414
You know anything more
about him?

40:49.481 --> 40:52.984
Just that his wife's
in the same company.
She travels a lot.

40:53.051 --> 40:55.887
You haven't met the wife?
No.

40:55.954 --> 40:58.089
Do you think you can get
back into his office?

40:58.156 --> 41:01.426
I don't see why not.
He's already left me alone
once in the house.

41:01.493 --> 41:04.462
He trusts you.
More than that.

41:04.530 --> 41:06.297
For a man
whose wife's out of town,

41:06.364 --> 41:08.500
he's a little too friendly,
if you know what I mean.

41:08.567 --> 41:10.569
I think you should
call the colonel.
Don't.

41:10.636 --> 41:13.138
It's probably
just another test.

41:13.204 --> 41:15.073
Maybe I wasn't supposed
to notice the brochure.

41:15.140 --> 41:19.645
But the better guess-- our
landing in this town with
these jobs is no accident.

41:19.711 --> 41:22.013
I don't understand.
Neither do I.

41:22.080 --> 41:23.982
But I'm going to.

41:26.552 --> 41:28.587
[ Tires Screeching ]

41:45.637 --> 41:48.039
- No one.
- Gone.

41:57.549 --> 41:59.618
Over here.

42:01.587 --> 42:05.023
Tire treads.
They switched vehicles.

42:05.090 --> 42:07.593
Maybe a van.
Put the girls in there,
drove off.

42:07.659 --> 42:10.161
Ah, they could be
anywhere by now.

42:17.368 --> 42:20.572
You made
the only choice you could.
Is that right?

42:20.639 --> 42:23.942
You had to get the plutonium.

42:24.009 --> 42:26.011
Think of the lives
you've saved.

42:29.014 --> 42:31.249
You had to buy the girls,
hand them over, or else--

42:31.316 --> 42:34.720
You know what.
Why don't you
stop talking.

42:34.786 --> 42:36.888
It doesn't help.
